						<div class="postbody">By <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">STA #$03</tt>, do you mean the unofficial instruction 89 03, which is at the position in the grid where <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">STA #ii</tt> would be if it were valid? This opcode is a 2-byte, 2-cycle NOP on 6502 and <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">BIT #ii</tt> on 65C02 and 65816.</div>

